{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:john.10",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "John 10",
    "summary": "Source text for John 10 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:1",
      "text": "Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that entereth not by the door into the sheepfold, but climbeth up some other way, the same is a thief and a robber.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:2",
      "text": "But he that entereth in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:3",
      "text": "To him the porter openeth; and the sheep hear his voice: and he calleth his own sheep by name, and leadeth them out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:4",
      "text": "And when he putteth forth his own sheep, he goeth before them, and the sheep follow him: for they know his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:5",
      "text": "And a stranger will they not follow, but will flee from him: for they know not the voice of strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:6",
      "text": "This parable spake Jesus unto them: but they understood not what things they were which he spake unto them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:7",
      "text": "Then said Jesus unto them again, Verily, verily, I say unto you, I am the door of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:8",
      "text": "All that ever came before me are thieves and robbers: but the sheep did not hear them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:9",
      "text": "I am the door: by me if any man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:10",
      "text": "The thief cometh not, but for to steal, and to kill, and to destroy: I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:11",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:12",
      "text": "But he that is an hireling, and not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, seeth the wolf coming, and leaveth the sheep, and fleeth: and the wolf catcheth them, and scattereth the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:13",
      "text": "The hireling fleeth, because he is an hireling, and careth not for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:14",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd, and know my sheep, and am known of mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:15",
      "text": "As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:16",
      "text": "And other sheep I have, which are not of this fold: them also I must bring, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:17",
      "text": "Therefore doth my Father love me, because I lay down my life, that I might take it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:18",
      "text": "No man taketh it from me, but I lay it down of myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again. This commandment have I received of my Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:19",
      "text": "There was a division therefore again among the Jews for these sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:20",
      "text": "And many of them said, He hath a devil, and is mad; why hear ye him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:21",
      "text": "Others said, These are not the words of him that hath a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:22",
      "text": "And it was at Jerusalem the feast of the dedication, and it was winter.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:23",
      "text": "And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon’s porch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:24",
      "text": "Then came the Jews round about him, and said unto him, How long dost thou make us to doubt? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:25",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, I told you, and ye believed not: the works that I do in my Father’s name, they bear witness of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:26",
      "text": "But ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep, as I said unto you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:27",
      "text": "My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:28",
      "text": "And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:29",
      "text": "My Father, which gave them me, is greater than all; and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father’s hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:30",
      "text": "I and my Father are one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:31",
      "text": "Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:32",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, Many good works have I shewed you from my Father; for which of those works do ye stone me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:33",
      "text": "The Jews answered him, saying, For a good work we stone thee not; but for blasphemy; and because that thou, being a man, makest thyself God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:34",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are gods?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:35",
      "text": "If he called them gods, unto whom the word of God came, and the scripture cannot be broken;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:36",
      "text": "Say ye of him, whom the Father hath sanctified, and sent into the world, Thou blasphemest; because I said, I am the Son of God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:37",
      "text": "If I do not the works of my Father, believe me not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:38",
      "text": "But if I do, though ye believe not me, believe the works: that ye may know, and believe, that the Father is in me, and I in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:39",
      "text": "Therefore they sought again to take him: but he escaped out of their hand,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:40",
      "text": "And went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized; and there he abode.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:41",
      "text": "And many resorted unto him, and said, John did no miracle: but all things that John spake of this man were true.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.10.42",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:42",
      "text": "And many believed on him there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
